description: The 28th Malabar naval exercise, hosted by India, starts on October 8 in the Bay of Bengal. Involving India, the US, Japan, and Australia, the exercise aims to enhance interoperability and address shared maritime challenges in the Indian Ocean and Indo-Pacific regions amid China's assertiveness.
title: Amid China's muscle-flexing, Malabar drill to start on October 8
DRDO tests of man-portable air defence shield successful

description: Haryana's single-phase assembly elections witnessed a nearly 67% voter turnout, lower than previous years' figures. Fatehabad district recorded the highest turnout exceeding 74%, while urban districts like Gurgaon reported lower participation at 57.2%. Overall, some districts like Nuh experienced a slight increase, with 72.2% voter turnout compared to 2019.
title: Haryana turnout 67%, only 54% in affluent Gurgaon

description: Farooq Abdullah dismisses the possibility of any post-poll alliance with BJP for forming the next government in J&K, emphasizing that such an alignment would be detrimental. Omar Abdullah and Iltija Mufti echo these sentiments, criticizing BJP's alleged attempts to undermine J&K's autonomy.
title: 'Will sit in oppn rather than ally with BJP': Farooq Abdullah

description: Indian Foreign Minister S Jaishankar will attend the SCO heads of government meeting in Islamabad on October 15-16 but will not discuss bilateral ties with Pakistan. Jaishankar underscored Pakistan's continued support for terrorism as a barrier to SAARC summits and emphasized regional integration efforts with neighboring countries like Bangladesh and Sri Lanka.
title: Talks on bilateral ties not on Pakistan visit agenda: S Jaishankar

description: The government reverts to recruiting railway officers through UPSC Civil Services and Engineering Services Exams, abandoning the IRMS system due to insufficient technical manpower. The decision aims to address the unique technical and non-technical requirements and cope with existing manpower shortages through re-engagement of retired officers.
title: Govt approves railway officers recruitment via engineering & civil services exams

description: The government will soon launch NULM 2.0 for urban poor, targeting six groups like domestic and gig workers. Eligible individuals can avail microcredit to start enterprises. A pilot in 25 cities will identify poor families and issue unique ID cards for welfare scheme access.
title: Livelihood mission 2.0 for urban poor to focus on 6 grps such as sanitation & gig workers

description: Congress is predicted to win decisively in Haryana, potentially securing up to 65 seats in the 90-member assembly. In Jammu & Kashmir, the NC-Congress-CPM alliance is likely to lead over BJP, but may fall short of a majority. These projections signal a boost for the INDIA bloc and concerns for BJP.
title: Exit polls forecast Cong win in Hry, give Cong-NC edge in J&K

description: Former India captain MS Dhoni is set to meet Chennai Super Kings' management in mid-October to decide on his participation in the next IPL season. The BCCI's new rule classifying him as an 'uncapped' player allows CSK to retain him for Rs 4 crore. A final decision will impact CSK's auction strategy.
title: MS Dhoni to meet CSK owners ahead of IPL mega auction

description: Supporters of former PM Imran Khan reached Islamabad's D-Chowk, countering heavy police presence and internet cuts. The Islamabad high court has ordered a designated protest zone. Khan's PTI challenges the ruling coalition, claiming election fraud and facing government crackdowns. Amnesty International criticized communication cuts and road blockades.
title: Islamabad on edge: Army deployed, internet shut as Imran Khan's supporters plan massive rally

description: Dalip Singh Rana, also known as The Great Khali, has an impressive car collection, including a Toyota Land Cruiser and a discontinued Ford Endeavour. The WWE Hall of Famer, famed as the first Indian-born World Heavyweight Champion, remains a celebrated figure in Indian sports and continues to influence wrestling in India.
title: Cars owned by 'The Great Khali': Swanky wagons of the WWE Hall of Famer

description: India will host the 28th Malabar naval exercise in the Bay of Bengal from October 8 to 18, involving the US, Japan, and Australia to enhance maritime cooperation. The exercise includes anti-submarine, surface warfare, and air defense operations. Participating naval forces will work to improve situational awareness and address shared maritime challenges in the Indo-Pacific.
title: Malabar exercise among 'Quad' countries to kick-off next week in Bay of Bengal
Trump goes nuclear for Israel

description: The Indian cricket team has experienced a setback with all-rounder Shivam Dube being ruled out of the T20I series against Bangladesh due to a back injury. Tilak Varma has been announced as his replacement for the three-match series starting on Sunday in Gwalior.
title: Shivam Dube ruled out of India-Bangladesh T20I series
Exit polls predict return of Cong govt in Haryana with big win over BJP
Poll of exit polls: Cong to sweep Haryana; alliance with NC has edge in J&K

description: Junior doctors in Kolkata initiated a hunger strike, demanding improved hospital security, 24-hour protection for healthcare workers, and an investigation into corruption. Triggered by recent violent incidents and inadequate safety measures, they threaten to continue protests until substantial government action is taken. ​​The doctors have also highlighted the culture of fear and intimidation within state-run hospitals, alleging that the administration has not provided a safe working environment.​
title: RG Kar case: Protesting doctors begin hunger strike against Mamata govt

description: Mumbai Indians face a tough decision-making task ahead of the mega auction, needing to select players for retention from a pool of superstars like Rohit Sharma, Hardik Pandya, Jasprit Bumrah, and Suryakumar Yadav and other young players. While team chemistry and fan interests are crucial, retention rules limit their choices.
title: 'Googly daal diya aapne': Surya on IPL captaincy
J&K exit poll: BJP predicted to emerge as single largest party in Jammu

description: The IDF conducted a successful military operation targeting Hezbollah infrastructure in southern Lebanon, involving Commando Brigade and elite Yahalom Unit. They destroyed weapons stockpiles, observation posts, missile launch sites, and tunnel shafts allegedly used by Hezbollah militants. Airstrikes coordinated during the operation eliminated numerous Hezbollah operatives.
title: 'Destroyed weapons, tunnels': Footage shows IDF's ground op against Hezbollah

description: A deadly gunfight in Pakistan's Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province resulted in the deaths of six soldiers, including an officer, and six terrorists. The exchange of fire occurred in North Waziristan district. The banned Tehreek-e-Taliban Pakistan (TTP) claimed responsibility for the attack.
title: Pakistan: Six soldiers, 6 TTP terrorists killed in gunfight
Himachal mosque row: Court orders demolition of 3 floors
Exit polls predict Congress sweep in Haryana: Top developments

description: Zomato CEO Deepinder Goyal and his wife Grecia Munoz took to the streets of Gurugram as delivery agents, fulfilling food orders themselves. The couple shared the experience on Instagram.
title: Zomato CEO ‘teams up’ with wife, turn delivery agent in Gurugram

description: The India vs Bangladesh T20I rivalry has produced iconic, nail-biting encounters such as the 2016 World Cup last-over thriller, Karthik's last-ball six in the 2018 Nidahas Trophy final, Dhoni's finishing prowess in the 2016 Asia Cup final, Chahar's record-breaking spell in Nagpur 2019, and Bangladesh's historic win in 2019.
title: Unforgettable India vs Bangladesh T20Is

description: Sanjay Manjrekar faced social media backlash for a perceived racist remark during the India vs New Zealand Women's T20 World Cup game commentary. Manjrekar admitted unfamiliarity with players from northern India, prompting fan outrage and calls for his sacking. India lost the match by 58 runs, with their next game against Pakistan.
title: 'Sack Him': Manjrekar draws flak for 'North India' players remark

description: BJP has sharply criticized Congress, alleging a woman was molested on stage during a Congress campaign event, with Congress MP Deepender Hooda present. Shehzad Poonawalla accused Congress of being anti-women, while Congress leader Kumari Selja demanded strict action against the accused party workers.
title: BJP shares video of woman 'molested' on stage at Cong event; Selja reacts

description: PDP leader Iltija Mufti criticized the upcoming government in Jammu and Kashmir as lacking real power, calling its chief minister a "rubber stamp." The remarks came just before assembly election results, amid claims that recent administrative changes undermine the new government's authority. Union home minister Amit Shah dismissed the allegations as false and speculative.
title: Incoming J&K govt will be 'toothless tiger', CM a 'rubber stamp': Iltija Mufti

description: Football boasts records like Lionel Messi's 91 goals in 2012, Pele's 1,279 career goals, and Just Fontaine's 13 goals in a single World Cup in 1958. Real Madrid's five consecutive European Cups (1956-1960) and Brazil's five World Cup victories highlight feats that appear almost impossible to beat in today's competitive landscape.
title: Top 5 unbeatable records in football: Milestones that may never be broken

description: A South African man, Nkosinathi Phakathi, has been sentenced to 42 life terms for assaulting schoolgirls and young women over nine years. Posing as an electrician, he gained entry into victims' homes, committing 90 rapes. Judge Makolomakwe condemned the heinous nature of his crimes. Phakathi’s other charges included kidnapping and assault.
title: Man gets 42 life terms in jail on 90 counts of rape

description: The NBA preseason began with a game in Abu Dhabi between the Boston Celtics and the Denver Nuggets. Sporting icons like Rohit Sharma, Thierry Henry, and Ronaldinho attended. Boston won 107-103. Players like Payton Pritchard and Nikola Jokic shone. The event highlighted the NBA's growing global presence and cross-sport engagement.
title: Watch: Rohit shares spotlight with Henry, Ronaldinho

description: External affairs minister S Jaishankar stated that during his visit for the Shanghai Cooperation Organisation, bilateral talks with Pakistan are ruled out, emphasizing that good relations hinge on addressing cross-border terrorism. He highlighted the differing views of Sardar Patel and Nehru on India-China ties.
title: Will India-Pak ties come up at SCO summit? What EAM Jaishankar said

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi visited Maharashtra, offering prayers, playing traditional instruments, and inaugurating the Banjara Virasat Museum. He also launched the Mumbai Metro Line 3 and its related MetroConnect3 app, while disbursing Rs 20,000 crore under PM-KISAN for farmers, impacting around 9.4 crore beneficiaries.
title: Watch: PM Modi tries his hands on a traditional dhol in Maharashtra

description: A 43-year-old man, Vetri Vendhan, was arrested by Tiruvallur town police for poisoning and killing 16 stray dogs that attacked his pigeons and hens. He was tracked through CCTV footage and confessed to the crimes, leading to his judicial custody under animal cruelty laws.
title: BSP leader arrested for killing 16 stray dogs in Tamil Nadu

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi accused the Congress party of divisive politics and links to a major drug racket during his visit to Maharashtra's Washim district. He also launched significant agricultural and animal husbandry projects worth Rs 23,300 crore, benefiting farmers and supporting marginalized communities.
title: Congress wants to push the youth towards drugs: PM Modi

description: The body of a 10-year-old girl was found in South 24 Parganas, West Bengal, triggering violent protests by locals, alleging her rape and murder. The police outpost was set ablaze, with demands for action against the delayed police response. An accused was arrested shortly after the complaint was lodged, and investigations are ongoing.
title: 'Rape, murdered, minor's body found in marshy land': Protests erupt in Bengal

description: Telegram, a popular messaging app, is revealed as a global hub for criminal activity, disinformation, and extremist content, facilitated by its emphasis on user privacy and minimal moderation. The New York Times investigation highlights its use by drug traffickers, weapons dealers, and terrorist groups, underscoring the urgent need for stricter oversight.
title: What went wrong with Telegram: ‘Live terrorist attack'; channels selling drugs, guns & more

description: Former Pakistan captain Salman Butt has defended Babar Azam following his resignation as white-ball captain, criticizing ex-pacer Sikander Bakht's harsh comments. Butt emphasized Babar's consistent contributions to Pakistan cricket over the last five years and argued that criticism should respect the player's stature, regardless of personal opinions.
title: 'Respect wahi deta hai jiski apni hoti hain': Butt defends Babar Azam

description: Ravichandran Ashwin expressed his concern over the current instability in Pakistan cricket, highlighting leadership chaos and poor performances. He noted that the constant captaincy changes are affecting the team's morale and cohesion. Ashwin emphasized Pakistan's lack of recent home Test match victories and believed that players are focusing more on individual performances due to the turmoil.
title: 'Makes me feel sorry': Ashwin on Pakistan cricket's turmoil

description: Rahul Gandhi criticized BJP over the collapse of Shivaji Maharaj's statue in Kolhapur, attributing it to their flawed ideology. He emphasized that the Congress party fights for the same principles Shivaji Maharaj upheld, aligning them with the Indian Constitution. He linked BJP's actions, including the exclusion of the tribal President, to ideological conflicts shaping upcoming Maharashtra elections.
title: 'No use of bowing before Shivaji after destroying Constitution': Rahul
Indigo airlines face system outage; slower check-ins, long queues at airport

description: Toyota has decided to end its sponsorship of cultural events like LGBTQ+ Pride in the US, citing the politicised debate around diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) programmes. The company will also stop participating in cultural surveys and the Human Rights Campaign’s Corporate Equality Index. This follows criticism from right-wing commentator Robby Starbuck, who opposes DEI initiatives. Toyota joins other companies, including Ford and Harley-Davidson, in reducing DEI efforts, despite research showing consumers, especially Gen Z, favour brands supporting the LGBTQ+ community.
title: Why Toyota will no longer sponsor LGBTQ+ Pride parades

description: Inmates in West Bengal correctional homes will enjoy a special menu featuring mutton biryani, 'basanti pulao,' and other Bengali dishes during Durga Puja. The initiative aims to uplift inmates' spirits from October 9 to October 12, with prisoners provided the choice to opt for vegetarian options respecting their religious sentiments.
title: 'Mutton biryani', 'basanti pulao' to be served to WB prisoners in Durga puja

description: BJP MP Naveen Jindal arrived on horseback to vote in the Haryana Assembly elections. Jindal, who recently switched from Congress to BJP, expressed pride in joining BJP and his commitment to PM Modi's vision. The election has 1,031 candidates vying for 90 seats, with results expected on October 8.
title: BJP MP Naveen Jindal reaches polling station on horse

description: Pacer Mayank Yadav seeks to prove his fitness and skill in India's T20 series against Bangladesh. With regulars rested, fringe players like Harshit Rana and Nitish Kumar aim to impress. Spinner Varun Chakaravarthy returns, while the series offers insight for IPL franchises ahead of the auction.
title: IND vs BAN T20I: Mayank Yadav set for fitness and form challenge

description: Andhra Pradesh CM N Chandrababu Naidu stated that devotees are satisfied with the improved quality of laddu prasadam at the Lord Venkateswara temple. He inaugurated the Vakulaamatha centralised kitchen and emphasized the use of high-quality ingredients. Naidu vowed to maintain the temple's sanctity and suggested reducing VIP culture at Tirumala.
title: 'VIP culture should be reduced in Tirumala': Chandrababu Naidu

description: Elon Musk’s platform X, banned by Supreme Court Justice Alexandre de Moraes over disinformation charges, mistakenly transferred $5.2 million in fines to the wrong account. Justice Moraes instructed the redirection of these funds. X, with 22 million Brazilian users, began blocking certain accounts and requested to lift the ban, which Moraes conditioned on paying pending fines.
title: Elon Musk's X transfers $5.2 million fine to wrong bank account
'Bharat Ratna for CM Nitish Kumar' posters seen outside Patna party office

description: India and Pakistan women’s cricket teams have met 15 times in T20 internationals. India has won 12 times, Pakistan three. The teams will face off again at the 2024 Women’s T20 World Cup. India must win all remaining matches after losing to New Zealand, while Pakistan are confident after beating Sri Lanka.
title: India vs Pakistan at Women's T20 World Cup: Recap of their encounters

description: The James Webb Space Telescope uncovers carbon dioxide and hydrogen peroxide on Pluto’s moon Charon. This discovery, published in Nature Communications, provides new insights into Charon's chemical composition, complementing earlier findings by NASA’s New Horizons spacecraft about its surface materials. This research advances understanding of organic reactions and solar radiation processes.
title: James Webb Telescope detects CO2 and hydrogen peroxide on Pluto’s largest moon Charon; know the insights

description: A special court in Pune has summoned Rahul Gandhi for alleged defamatory remarks against Vinayak Damodar Savarkar. The complaint, filed by Satyaki Savarkar, claims Gandhi's 2023 speech contained false statements. Gandhi is to appear in court on October 23, facing charges under Section 500 of the Indian Penal Code after police found prima facie evidence.
title: Pune court summons Rahul Gandhi in defamation case over remarks on Savarkar

description: Hackers have scammed thousands using fake trade apps available on Google Play and Apple App Store, as reported by Group-IB. These fraudulent apps, part of the UniShadowTrade malware family, manipulated victims into depositing funds on fake platforms under the guise of high returns. Once removed from app stores, scammers shifted to phishing websites.
title: These 'fake' trading apps on your phones are helping hackers

description: A fire severely damaged the Notre-Dame-des-Sept-Allégresses church in Trois-Rivières, causing the collapse of a bell tower. Built in 1914, the church was set for conversion into residential homes. The cause of the fire remains under investigation.
title: Watch: Historic Canadian church in Quebec goes up in flames

description: The October 4th episode of WWE SmackDown featured the return of AJ Styles, who faced Carmelo Hayes but lost due to a leg injury. Michin defeated Chelsea Green in a Dumpster Match, Naomi overcame Tiffany Stratton, and The Bloodline retained their tag team titles against DIY and The Street Profits.
title: WWE SmackDown 10/4: Carmelo Hayes vs. AJ Styles, Dumpster Match

description: Swiggy launched its 10-minute food delivery service 'Bolt' in select cities including Bengaluru, Chennai, Hyderabad, New Delhi, Mumbai, and Pune. Partnering with over 2,700 restaurants, Bolt aims to deliver quick-to-prepare items. This follows Swiggy's preparation for its IPO, targeting a valuation up to $13 billion.
title: Swiggy launches new 10-min food delivery service launched in these cities

description: The BCCI has changed the IPL retention rules, altering the Right to Match (RTM) process. Franchises are concerned about the new rule allowing the highest bidder to raise their bid before the RTM is used. They argue it undermines the RTM's purpose, potentially discouraging retention and affecting the overall auction strategy.
title: Concerns over new RTM clause: Franchises write to BCCI ahead of IPL auction

description: India's hopes of making the semifinals of the ICC Women's T20 World Cup 2024 are in jeopardy after a 58-run loss to New Zealand. To qualify, India must win their remaining three group matches against Pakistan, Sri Lanka, and Australia with significant margins to improve their net run rate and hope for other results to go in their favour.
title: Women's T20 WC scenario: What India must do to qualify for semifinals

description: Haryana MLA Balraj Kundu, leader of the Haryana Jan Sevak Party, accuses former MLA Anand Singh Dangi of physically assaulting him and his personal assistant during a heated election dispute in Meham. Kundu attributes the alleged attack to Dangi's frustration over his electoral prospects.
title: Watch: Rebel MLA groups break into fight at Haryana's Meham

description: Sachin Kurmi, a leader of the NCP's Ajit Pawar faction, was murdered in Mumbai's Byculla area. He was attacked with a sharp-edged weapon by unidentified assailants around 12:30 am. Police have registered a case and investigations are ongoing to identify the attackers.
title: NCP leader Sachin Kurmi murdered in South Mumbai

description: Chandan Verma, the prime suspect in the murders of a Dalit school teacher and his family in Amethi, was injured during a police encounter as he was being escorted to recover the murder weapon. The victims, Sunil Kumar, his wife, and their two young daughters, were found shot dead in their home with no signs of forced entry.
title: Amethi family murder: Accused Chandan Verma shot in police encounter

description: US Vice President Kamala Harris appeared on Alex Cooper's podcast 'Call Her Daddy' to discuss reproductive rights in the US. The episode is aimed at engaging young female listeners, highlighting the significance of connecting with younger audiences. Harris' campaign emphasizes her media engagement focusing on social media reach and the cultural relevance of Cooper’s show.
title: Kamala Harris appears on 'Call Her Daddy' podcast to discuss abortion

description: During a town hall in North Carolina, Donald Trump announced plans for a panel to exclude "woke generals" from the Defence Department. He also pledged to raise military pay, build a missile defense system, and restore Fort Liberty's original name, appealing to military supporters.
title: Trump promises to keep 'woke generals' out of US defence department

description: Security forces conducted a joint operation in Kupwara, Jammu and Kashmir, neutralising two terrorists after detecting an infiltration attempt. The operation, involving the Indian Army and Jammu and Kashmir Police, saw an exchange of fire and recovery of war-like stores, with searches in the area still ongoing.
title: J&K: Security forces eliminate two terrorists in Kupwara operation

description: Police in Chhattisgarh's Bastar region have recovered additional bodies of three Maoists, raising the death toll to 31 following a fierce encounter with security forces. Spanning a 10km area in Abujhmarh, the gunfight lasted from 1 pm to 9 pm. Security forces retrieved automatic firearms and explosives, marking the highest Maoist casualty in a single operation since the state's formation.
title: 3 more Maoists found dead after Bastar encounter; toll rises to 31

description: Indian women's cricket team faced a 58-run defeat against New Zealand at the Dubai International Stadium. Shafali Verma, Smriti Mandhana, and Harmanpreet Kaur's early dismissals led to a dismal batting performance, chasing 161. Despite efforts in fielding and fitness, errors allowed New Zealand to capitalize and post a challenging total.
title: Women's T20 WC: India crash to a 58-run defeat against New Zealand

description: Hockey India is reviving the Hockey India League (HIL) after seven years. The league will feature eight men's teams and six women's teams. Significant investments will attract top global players. A dedicated window between December and February is set for the competition, with no other competitions in that period. The league will span ten years.
title: Rs 3640 crore to be spent over 10 years on revived Hockey India League

description: Apple's new iPhone 16 series is now on sale, and as one would have expected, they bring new features on board – Apple Intelligence is a big one of them. You might be wondering if you should upgrade or which new iPhone to buy. Well, worry not; this guide will help you navigate the options and decide which new iPhone is right for you in 2024. Whether you're upgrading from an older iPhone or curious about what's new, this guide breaks down everything you need to know about the iPhone 16 lineup.
title: iPhone 16 buying guide: Which new iPhone model should you buy and why

description: Chief minister Nara Chandrababu Naidu presented silk robes to Lord Venkateswara at the Tirumala temple for the 14th time, coinciding with the start of the annual Brahmotsavams. He released TTD's 2025 calendars and participated in rituals, including Pedda Sesha vahanam. The TTD and officials oversaw the smooth commencement of the nine-day festival.
title: Andhra CM Naidu presents silk robes at Tirumala temple amid laddu row

description: Yasin Malik, chairman of Jammu & Kashmir Liberation Front-Yasin (JKLF-Y), declared in an affidavit that he renounced armed struggle for a peaceful resolution of the Kashmir issue in 1994, opting for a 'Gandhian way of resistance.' Despite his claims of engaging with central government officials for dialogue, JKLF-Y remains banned for five more years.
title: Have quit 'armed struggle' in 1984, turned Gandhian: Yasin Malik

description: Taiwan's Ministry of Defence reported detecting 13 Chinese military aircraft and 3 naval vessels encircling the island after a short lull. Eight aircraft crossed the median line into Taiwan's air defense identification zone. This follows a pattern of increased Chinese military activities near Taiwan, involving regular air and naval incursions since September 2020.
title: Taiwan detects renewed Chinese military activity, 'responds accordingly'

description: Donald Trump urged Israel to strike Iran's nuclear facilities after a missile attack, criticizing Joe Biden's restraint. Trump advocated for an aggressive response, while Biden emphasized proportional retaliation to avoid escalating conflict. Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu is evaluating potential responses, including symbolic or direct actions.
title: 'Hit Iran's nuclear ...': Trump on how Israel should respond to missile attack

description: In Amethi, a Dalit schoolteacher, his wife, and two daughters were brutally murdered by Chandan Verma, who was in love with the teacher's wife, Poonam Bharti. Police claim Sunil Kumar discovered his wife's affair, prompting Chandan's vengeful attack after lodging a harassment FIR against him.
title: Amethi family murder: 'Killer was in relationship with teacher's wife'
